(Text form): 

BioInformatics: Introduction 

Wikipedia website: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bioinformatics

General defintiion (from Wikipedia): 

"A field that develops methods and software tools for understanding biological data. As an interdisciplinary field of science, bioinformatics combines computer science, statistics, mathematics, and engineering to analyze and interpret biological data. Bioinformatics has been used for in silico analyses of biological queries using mathematical and statistical techniques." 

Broken down, BioInformatics basically divides up the inter-discplinary field into 3 main spheres: 
(written out verbatim due to small text shown in the diagram) 

