General Applications regards to CILSE research (from computing):

- sequence alignment (Needleman-Wunsh Algorithm / Optimal Matching) 
Uses: determine accuracy of a matching, determine the penalty for gaps / mismatches (transformations and mutations) within two or more unique DNA sequences, determine the edit distance between nucleotides of the DNA sequences, and application to genomics / BLAST sequencing
- Machine Learning
Uses: determine how accurate / precise an algorithm is used to match DNA sequences / genetic inference of the DNA / classification learning / BLAST sequencing 
- Throughput / Systems:
Uses: Amdahl's (to determine which computing system can compute the result faster, comparison within distributed systems for biological processes),  image resolution processing, genomics 
- Databases / DNA querying: 
Uses: MoClo computing, Alignment Verification (to determine if user input is valid or not), hierarchy of DNA sequences, SQL / Mongo DNA querying (as used in Clotho UI and Living Computing Project's Clotho work) 

- Programming Software (divided into software and hardware components): 


